cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.SI, cs.DS 

This paper is likely to belong to the category of Computer Science - Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) as it describes a distributed platform for collecting information about user activity in peer-to-peer systems, which is a key but challenging task in the field of security. It may also belong to the categories of Computer Science - Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) and Computer Science - Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) as it deals with measuring activity on a peer-to-peer network and using honeypots to collect data. Additionally, it may belong to the categories of Computer Science - Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) and Computer Science - Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) as it involves analyzing data obtained from the measurement system and studying the impact of key parameters.
